11/02/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government will prepare an Action Plan for cutting ministers' discretionary rights in an effort to curb corruption, Justice Minister Meri Mladenovska-Gjorgjievska announced Thursday (10 February). Agreement was reached during a joint meeting of government representatives, an expert team, an anti-corruption commission and the NGO Transparency Macedonia. Mladenovska-Gjorgjievska explained that the action plan is intended to introduce better monitoring and control by the public. (MIA, A1 TV - 10/02/05)
